Text.Value: I don't understand. The blow should have only knocked him out, not killed him.
Go on up, pay Gortash a visit. A fete to remember, I guarantee.

EditorData.logicalname: Not to ceremony yet, but sent

Text.Value: Poor thing. He's had a tough go - and you don't know the half of it.
Ravengard's good as dead. And to think, there's no way to save him.
What are you getting at?
Let's meet in your camp, lay everything out.
Relocated? What are you playing at, devil?
And to think the drama's just started.
Such a shame. And to think there's no way to save him.

EditorData.NodeContext: Very cheekily. She know she holds all the cards

Text.Value: Where's he been taken?
Or is there?
Rude. This is Gortash's game. I'm just an impartial observer.
You see, Gortash has had Wyll's father... relocated.
I know enough. Let's talk to Wyll in your camp, work something out.
He's upstairs in Wyrm's Rock, ordaining Gortash as Archduke.
The Duke's life is not all that's at stake.
Who knows? Let him die for all I care.
Let's meet Wyll in your camp, work something out.
I'm saying that someone stepping off stage doesn't have to mean the end of their story.
Damn right he is. And he better stay that way.
I'm just an impartial observer - this is Gortash's game. A murderous one, the way I hear it.
Or is he?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: A diabolical circle draws underneath Mizora. She descends into it and it closes behind her.
EditorData.SFXTags: [KC] A diabolical circle draws underneath Mizora. She descends into it and it closes behind her.
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] A diabolical circle draws underneath Mizora. She descends into it and it closes behind her.

Text.Value: Are you saying Ravengard's not gone for good?
I'd hate for him to miss the fun.
Heard about his father. The Dead Three's puppet - a travesty, really.
To his death, the way I hear it.
My, aren't we eager?
You may not care - but Wyll does.
The Duke's life depends on it.
You know something, don't you?
I'm not giving up on the duke. Tell me what to do.
Meet me in your camp. I've got a devil of a proposal.
A splendid shindig, I hear - perfect for crashing. Go on up - we'll talk after. And bring the pup along if you can.
What did I tell you? A momentous occasion, I'm sure you agree.
Poor little Wyll. Such a tragedy - his own father, cut down in his prime. Damn shame, if you ask me.
If it isn't little Wyll's chums. I hope he hasn't been too much trouble.
You say that. But minds can change in the span of a snap.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Mizora snaps her fingers with the word 'snap'.

Text.Value: That was fast. I thought Gortash would have more use for the duke in Wyrm's Rock.
A man of the people, the grandest of dukes. Hard to think he's forever lost to us.
*Mizora responds with knowing silence - and a wide smile.*

Synopsis: Dialog with mizora at Wyrm's Rock near the entrance to Lower city. You see Ravengard taken away, and Mizora tells you to meet him in camp. Version if Wyll is not there.
